Nathi Veronica Ngomane was arrested on May 28 almost two years after the gruesome murder of the 34-year-old Nkosi, who was kidnapped from his house at KaGudlane section in Msogwaba on October 9, 2018. He was assaulted by a group in front of his then 14-year-old daughter before being forced into a white Nissan. His assailants then fled with him. ALSO READ: Here are the Lowveld’s most recent dam levels Nkosi’s burned and mutilated body was found seven days later in a bush in Spelanyane Village. The provincial police have launched a manhunt for about ten other suspects linked to the crime.